<html xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:w="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Job Aid Source Template</title>
<style>
body { font-family: Aptos, Arial, sans-serif; color: #172033; line-height: 1.45; }
h1 { color: #17395c; border-bottom: 3px solid #1f5f99; padding-bottom: 8px; }
h2 { color: #1f5f99; margin-top: 24px; }
.guidance { color: #475569; background: #f1f5f9; border-left: 4px solid #60a5fa; padding: 8px 12px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Job Aid Source Template</h1>
<p class="guidance">Replace the guidance text in each section with your content, save the file, then upload it to the Learning Asset Builder. Keep the headings unchanged so the parser can map content accurately.</p>

<h2>Title</h2>
<p>[Enter the job aid title. Example: Process a Customer Refund]</p>

<h2>Task Overview</h2>
<p>[Describe the task this job aid supports in 1-3 concise sentences.]</p>

<h2>Audience</h2>
<p>[Describe who will use this job aid. Include role, team, experience level, or location if relevant.]</p>

<h2>Before You Begin</h2>
<p>[List required access, prerequisites, tools, systems, approvals, or information the user needs before starting.]</p>

<h2>Steps or Decision Points</h2>
<ol>
<li>[Enter the first action the user performs.]</li>
<li>[Enter the next action.]</li>
<li>[Continue until the task is complete.]</li>
</ol>
<p>If this is a decision aid, replace the numbered steps with decision points such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>If [condition], then [action].</li>
<li>If [condition], then [action].</li>
</ul>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<p>[Add realistic examples, completed fields, sample scenarios, or before/after examples.]</p>

<h2>Screenshots</h2>
<p>[Describe each screenshot needed and where it should appear. Upload the actual screenshot images separately in the app.]</p>

<h2>Tips</h2>
<p>[Add plain-language tips, shortcuts, reminders, quality checks, or common mistakes to avoid.]</p>

<h2>References</h2>
<p>[List source documents, policy links, system names, SMEs, or other references used to create this job aid.]</p>
</body>
</html>
